iser or a daughter. ...\" ... \"Especially since she was last in the news as a senior adviser going to the Olympics.\u201d ... \u201cshe did choose to play this senior advisory role.\u201d)}}</ref> even though that is actually the title of her husband [[Jared Kushner]], while her own title is 'Advisor to the President'.<ref name=WhiteHouse2018-12-18a>{{cite web |title=Press Briefing by Press Secretary Sarah Sanders|url=https://www.whitehouse.gov/briefings-statements/press-briefing-by-press-secretary-sarah-sanders-121818/|date= 18 December 2018|accessdate=4 May 2019 |publisher=[[Executive Office of the President of the United States|The White House]]|quote=MS. SANDERS:  ... the World Economic Forum ... delegation ... will also include ..., Advisor to the President Ivanka Trump, Senior Advisor to the President Jared Kushner, ...}}</ref>}}<br />{{small|(born 1981)}}\n|Strategic Planning<ref name=\"djt1\">{{cite press release |last=Trump |first=Donald J. |date=March 27, 2017 |title=Presidential Memorandum on The White House Office of American Innovation |url=https://www.whitehouse.gov/the-press-office/2017/03/27/presidential-memorandum-white-house-office-american-innovation |location= |publisher=The White House |quote=The Senior Advisor to the President.}}</ref><ref name=\"spicer29\">{{cite web|url=https://www.whitehouse.gov/the-press-office/2017/03/27/press-briefing-press-secretary-sean-spicer-3272017-29|title=Press Briefing by Press Secretary Sean Spicer, #29|date=March 27, 2017|publisher=The White House|via=[[whitehouse.gov]]|url-status=dead|quote=The effort will be led by Assistant to the President and Senior Adviser Jared Kushner.}}</ref>\n|January 20, 2017 \u2013 present<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/post-politics/wp/2017/01/09/tumps-son-in-law-jared-kushner-expected-to-join-white-house-as-a-senior-adviser/|title=Trump\u2019s son-in-law, Jared Kushner, to join White House as senior adviser; no formal role for Ivanka Trump|last=Wagner|firs