ublican]]\n|- \n! style=\"background:{{Republican Party (United States)/meta/color}};\" |\n|[[file:Ivanka Trump official portrait (cropped).jpg|100px|Ivanka Trump]]\n|[[Ivanka Trump]]<ref group=\"n\" name=IvankaNotSenior01a/><br />{{small|(born 1981)}}\n|Women's Issues<br />Policy\n|March 28, 2017 \u2013 present<ref name=\"White House Office, June 30, 2017\">{{cite web|url=https://www.whitehouse.gov/sites/whitehouse.gov/files/docs/disclosures/07012017-report-final.pdf|title=Executive Office Of The President Annual Report To Congress On White House Office Personnel White House Office As Of: Friday, June 30, 2017|publisher=The White House|page=15|language=English|via=[[whitehouse.gov]]|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20170630223857/https://www.whitehouse.gov/sites/whitehouse.gov/files/docs/disclosures/07012017-report-final.pdf|archivedate=June 30, 2017|accessdate=June 30, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cnn.com/2017/03/29/politics/ivanka-trump-white-house-job/index.html|title=Ivanka Trump is making her White House job official|last=Merica|first=Dan|date=March 30, 2017|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190308011951/https://www.cnn.com/2017/03/29/politics/ivanka-trump-white-house-job/index.html|archive-date=March 8, 2019|publisher=[[CNN]]|last2=Borger|first2=Gloria|last3=Acosta|first3=Jim|last4=Klein|first4=Betsy|author-link2=Gloria Borger|author-link3=Jim Acosta}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://apnews.com/2b3bab9741604a448e1c2b8bd49e6931|title=Ivanka Trump\u2019s dual roles as senior adviser, first daughter|last=Lucey|first=Catherine|date=February 26, 2018|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180314154433/https://apnews.com/2b3bab9741604a448e1c2b8bd49e6931|archive-date=March 14, 2018|agency=[[Associated Press]]}}</ref>\n|[[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]<ref name=\"KushnerVice\"/>\n|-\n! style=\"background:{{Republican Party (United States)/meta/color}};\" |\n|[[file:Kevin Hassett official photo.jpg|100px|Kevin Hassett]]\n|[[Kevin Hassett]]<br />{{small|(born 1962)}}\n|Economic issues\n|April 15, 2020 \u2013 present<ref name=\"White House Office, April 15, 2020\">{{cite web|url=https://www.whitehouse.gov/briefings-statements/president-donald-j-trump-announces-addition-white-house-staff/|title=President Donald J. Trump Announces Addition to White House Staff|publisher=The White House|language=English|via=[[whitehouse.gov]]|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|[[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]\n|}\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|United States|Politics}}\n* [[Counselor to the President]]\n* [[White House Chief Strategist]]\n\n==Footnotes==\n{{reflist|group=n}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n{{Senior Advisors to the President}}\n{{White House Office}}\n{{EOP agencies}}\n\n[[Category:Executive Office of the President of the United States]]\n[[Category:White House Office]]\n[[Category:United States presidential advisors]]\n[[Category:1993 establishments in Washington, D.C.]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=May 2017}}\n\n{{Infobox US Cabinet\n|post         = Senior Advisor\n|insignia     = US-WhiteHouse-Logo.svg\n|insigniasize = 175\n|image        = {{multiple image|align=center|image1 = Jared Kushner cropped.jpg| width1 =60|image2=Stephen Miller by Gage Skidmore.jpg| width2 =60|image3=Ivanka Trump official photo.jpg| width3 =60|image4=Kevin Hassett official photo.jpg| width4=60 }}\n|department   = [[Executive Office of the President]]\n|incumbent    = [[Jared Kushner]], [[Stephen Miller (political operative)|Stephen Miller]], [[Ivanka Trump]], [[Kevin Hassett]]\n|website      = [https://www.whitehouse.gov/ The White House]\n}}\n'''Senior Advisor to the President''' is a title used by high-ranking political advisors to the [[president of the United States]]. White House senior advisors are senior members of the [[White House Office]]. The title has been formally used since 1993.\n\n==Responsibilities==\nOver time, the senior advisor role has had responsibility for the following groups:\n\n* [[White House Office of Strategic Initiatives]]\n* [[Office of American Innovation]]\n* [[White House Office of Intergovernmental Affairs]]\n* [[White House Office#Office of Political Affairs|White House Office of Political Affairs]]\n* [[Office of Public Liaison]]\n* [[White House Communications Director]]\n\n==Prior administrations==\nIn prior administrations before 1993, the position of \"senior advisor\" was a title used for various other purposes. Numerous examples of the position also exist throughout the [[United States federal executive departments|Executive Departments]] and in the branch's [[Independent agencies of the United States government|independent agencies]]. For example, the [[Food and Drug Administration]] includes a position with the title Senior Advisor for Science; the [[United States Department of the Interior|Department of the Interior]] has a position with the title Senior Advisor for [[Alaska]]n Affairs.\n\n==List of senior advisors to the president==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! colspan=\"3\" |Senior Advisor\n!Portfolio\n!Term of office\n!Party\n!President\n|-\n! style=\"background:{{Democratic Party (United States)/meta/color}};\" |{{anchor|Bill Clinton}} \n|[[File:Chicago Mayor Rahm Emanuel 2012 (cropped).jpg|100px|Rahm Emanuel]]\n|[[Rahm Emanuel]]<br />{{small|(born 1959)}}\n|Political Affairs<br />Strategic Planning<br />Policy \n|January 20, 1993 \u2013 November 7, 1998<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cityofchicago.org/city/en/depts/mayor/supp_info/about_the_mayor.html|title=City of Chicago :: About the Mayor|publisher=}}</ref>\n|[[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]\n| rowspan=\"5\" |[[Bill Clinton]]\n|-\n! style=\"background:{{Democratic Party (United States)/meta/color}};\" |\n|[[File:George Stephanopoulos cropped.jpg|100px|George Stephanopoulos]]\n|[[George Stephanopoulos]]<br />{{small|(born 1961)}}\n|Strategic Planning<br />Policy\n|Jun