land, 1997, {{ISBN|0-7864-0372-1}}.\n*[[Nathan Stoltzfus]], ''Hitler's Compromises : Coercion and Consensus in Nazi Germany'', New Haven: Yale University Press, 2016, {{ISBN|978-0300220995}}. \n* Noakes, J. (1978) \"The Oldenburg Crucifix Struggle of November 1936: A Case Study of Opposition in the Third Reich\". In P. Stachura (Ed.), ''The Shaping of the Nazi State.'' London: Croom Helm.\n*<nowiki>https://urldefense.proofpoint.com/v2/url?u=http-3A__www.spiegel.de_spiegel_print_d-2D46275329.html&d=DwICAg&c=MNHwOqQ8N1u91SoMLfIblwuGXKgp50OPUXjl8uRAbak&r=PswVdOAv8DiUuuJs-CMjsFke9n7L_SZNbonbhhgx0Yc&m=fRZqqejQmeMsCTKZ97y79zpeNp7MQT9LubcItPkPOlo&s=qDGqCyN_CWYqnIeRVtomny2KKrAg3EQPCuOQUHpEW4E&e=</nowiki> \n* Fest, Joachim C., (1997). ''Plotting Hitler's Death : the Story of the German resistance'' (1st Owl book ed.). New York: H. Holt and Co. {{ISBN|0080504213}}. {{OCLC|37626211}}.\n* Robert., Gellately, (2001). ''Backing Hitler : Consent and Coercion in Nazi Germany''. Oxford: OUP Oxford. {{ISBN|978-0191604522}}. {{OCLC|955228505}}.\n* Bukey, Evan Burr, (2000). ''Hitler's Austria : popular sentiment in the Nazi era, 1938\u20131945''. Mazal Holocaust Collection. Chapel Hill: University of North Carolina Press. {{ISBN|0807825166}}. {{OCLC|40907702}}\n* Baranowski, Shelley. \"Consent and Dissent: The Confessing Church and Conservative Opposition to National Socialism,\" The Journal of Modern History 59, no. 1 (Mar., 1987): 53\u201378.\n* Barnett, Victoria, (1992). ''For the soul of the people : Protestant protest against Hitler''. New York: Oxford University Press. {{ISBN|0585246513}}. {{OCLC|45734024}}\n* L., Bergen, Doris (1996). ''Twisted cross : the German Christian movement in the Third Reich''. Chapel Hill: University of North Carolina Press. {{ISBN|0585026513}}. {{OCLC|42329240}}\n* Richard, Bonney, (2009). ''Confronting the Nazi war on Christianity : the Kulturkampf newsletters, 1936\u20131939''. Oxford: Peter Lang. {{ISBN|978-3039119042}}. {{OCLC|432595116}}\n* Benda